ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Current programming version
True positive responses
False positive responses
Median response time for all correct responses
True positive responses for 0-back trials
False positive responses for 0-back trials
Median response time for correct 0-back trials (ms)
True positive responses for 1-back trials
False positive responses for 1-back trials
Median response time for correct 1-back trials (ms)
True positive responses for 2-back trials
False positive responses for 2-back trials
Median response time for correct 2-back trials (ms)
Sum of true positive responses for 1-back and 2-back trials
Median response time for true positive responses for 1-back and 2-back trials (ms)
Efficiency score LNB_MCR/log(LNB_MRTC)
Longest run of non-responses
Final run of non-responses (at end of the test)
Form used/assessment name
Notes: e.g., Self-Report, Parent Form, Short Form, Revised Version

ElementDescription: True positive responses for 3-back trials
False positive responses for 3-back trials
True positive responses for 4-back trials
False positive responses for 4-back trials
Order that the word sets are presented
Counts the number of times ''pos-pos-pos'' trials were run during the test blocks
Proportion correct ''pos-pos-pos'' trials across the test blocks
Counts the number of times ''pos-neg-pos'' trials were run during the test blocks
Proportion correct ''pos-neg-pos'' trials across the test blocks
Counts the number of times ''neg-neg-neg'' trials were run during the test blocks
Proportion correct ''neg-neg-neg'' trials across the test blocks
Counts the number of times ''neg-pos-neg'' trials were run during the test blocks
Proportion correct ''neg-pos-neg'' trials across the test blocks
The version/build of Inquisit
The platform the script was run on (win/mac/ios/android)
Date script was run
Assigned group ID number
Identifier of Testing Session
Time it took to run script (in ms); measured from onset to offset of script
Whether script was completed
Notes: 0 = Script was not completed (prematurely aborted); 1 = Script was completed (all conditions run)
